'''Kendall Jagdeosingh''' (born May 30, 1986 in [[Manzanilla, Trinidad and Tobago|Manzanilla]]) is a [[Trinidad and Tobago|Trinidadian]] [[association football|footballer]] who currently plays for [[Ayutthaya F.C.|Ayutthaya]] in [[Thai League 3]]
==Career==
===Club=== Jagdeosingh began his career in his native Trinidad, playing four seasons for [[North East Stars F.C.|North East Stars]] and [[Caledonia AIA]] in the [[TT Pro League]].
Jagdeosingh joined the [[Puerto Rico Islanders]] in the [[USL First Division]] in 2007. He helped the Islanders win the 2008 USL First Division regular season title and progressed to the semi finals of the [[CONCACAF Champions League 2008–09]].
On February 16, 2011, Jagdeosingh signed with [[Rochester Rhinos]] of the third division [[USL Pro]] league. The contract is for one year with a club option for 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oursportscentral.com/services/releases/?id=4154592 |title=Rhinos Sign Kendall Jagdeosingh - OurSports Central - Independent and Minor League Sports News |publisher=OurSports Central |date=2011-02-16 |accessdate=2012-01-11}}</ref>
In March 2012, Jagdeosing signed with [[Chainat F.C.]] alongside fellow Trinidad national [[Yohance Marshall]].
===International=== Jagdeosingh played for the Trinidadian national U-20 U-21 U-23 team, and was part of the Trinidad squad which competed at the [[2007 CONCACAF Gold Cup]]. He also participated in several of Trinidad's early qualifying games for the [[2010 FIFA World Cup]]. and qualifying games for the 2014 fifa World Cup and an international friendly against Finland on January 22, 2012
==Honors==
